<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="179" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="179">Distribution and habitat.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="179">Jiangxi Province, and Minjiang basin in Fujian Province. The crabs were found under rocks in mountain streams.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="179" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="179">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="179">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Y. S. Li, in Y. S. Li, J. N. Lin, Y. Z. Chen &amp; J. H. Tang" authorityYear="1985" class="Malacostraca" family="Potamidae" genus="Sinopotamon" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Sinopotamon wuyiensis" order="Decapoda" pageId="0" pageNumber="179" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="wuyiensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="179">Sinopotamon wuyiensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was considered a new species based on its distinct morphological characters in both male and female specimens, especially in the male specimen having a pair of vulvae on sternite 6, which is not seen in any known species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bott" authorityYear="1967" class="Malacostraca" family="Potamidae" genus="Sinopotamon" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Sinopotamon" order="Decapoda" pageId="0" pageNumber="179" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="179">Sinopotamon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Unfortunately, the type material of 
<taxonomicName genus="S." lsidName="S. wuyiensis" pageId="0" pageNumber="179" rank="species" species="wuyiensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="179">S. wuyiensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, which was originally deposited in Fujian Research Institute of Parasite Disease, Fuzhou, Fujian Province, is now lost (Youzhu Cheng, pers. comm.). Therefore, to investigate the status and validity of 
<taxonomicName genus="S." lsidName="S. wuyiensis" pageId="0" pageNumber="179" rank="species" species="wuyiensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="179">S. wuyiensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, we conducted comprehensive collections in Tongmu Village but found no record of 
<taxonomicName genus="S." lsidName="S. wuyiensis" pageId="0" pageNumber="179" rank="species" species="wuyiensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="179">S. wuyiensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the area. Instead, we collected 21 new specimens from 14 localities within the area (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figure 1. Localities of the sampling sites for Huananpotamon koatenense and Sinopotamon fukienense in the Wuyishan National Park, Fujian." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1112.85278.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/715096" pageId="0" pageNumber="179">1</figureCitation>
), all of which were identified as 
<taxonomicName genus="S." lsidName="S. fukienense" pageId="0" pageNumber="179" rank="species" species="fukienense">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="179">S. fukienense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by morphological comparison (Figs 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Sinopotamon fukienense, male, 23.2 x 29.0 mm, NNU 11 B- 211121 SF 1 A dorsal overall view ventral B view of anterior thoracic sternum and pleon C frontal view D ventral view of sterno-pleonal cavity with right G 1 in situ (left G 1 removed). Scale bars: 1.0 cm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1112.85278.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/715097" pageId="0" pageNumber="179">2</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figure 3. Sinopotamon fukienense, female, 22.5 x 29.0 mm, NNU 11 B- 211219 SF 14 A ventral view of pleon B ventral view showing female vulvae. Scale bars: 1.0 cm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1112.85278.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/715098" pageId="0" pageNumber="179">3</figureCitation>
). According to the original description of 
<taxonomicName genus="S." lsidName="S. wuyiensis" pageId="0" pageNumber="179" rank="species" species="wuyiensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="179">S. wuyiensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, apart from the unique male sternite 6, 
<taxonomicName genus="S." lsidName="S. wuyiensis" pageId="0" pageNumber="179" rank="species" species="wuyiensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="179">S. wuyiensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is identical with 
<taxonomicName genus="S." lsidName="S. fukienense" pageId="0" pageNumber="179" rank="species" species="fukienense">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="179">S. fukienense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in most characters, including outer margin of external orbital angle lined with 5-7 granules (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Sinopotamon fukienense, male, 23.2 x 29.0 mm, NNU 11 B- 211121 SF 1 A dorsal overall view ventral B view of anterior thoracic sternum and pleon C frontal view D ventral view of sterno-pleonal cavity with right G 1 in situ (left G 1 removed). Scale bars: 1.0 cm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1112.85278.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/715097" pageId="0" pageNumber="179">2A</figureCitation>
; cf. 
<bibRefCitation author="Dai, AY" journalOrPublisher="Acta Zoologica Sinica" pageId="0" pageNumber="179" pagination="243 - 249" refId="B8" refString="Dai, AY, Chen, GX, 1979. On the freshwater crabs from Fujian Province. Acta Zoologica Sinica 25: 243 - 249" title="On the freshwater crabs from Fujian Province." volume="25" year="1979">Dai and Chen 1979</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Li, YS" journalOrPublisher="Wuyi Science Journal" pageId="0" pageNumber="179" pagination="141 - 146" refId="B19" refString="Li, YS, Lin, JX, Cheng, YZ, Tang, JH, 1985. A new species of Sinopotamon crab harbouring metacercariae of lung flukes from the Wuyishan National Reserve, Fujian (Decapoda: Sinopotamonidae). Wuyi Science Journal 5: 141 - 146" title="A new species of Sinopotamon crab harbouring metacercariae of lung flukes from the Wuyishan National Reserve, Fujian (Decapoda: Sinopotamonidae)." volume="5" year="1985">Li et al. 1985</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Dai, AY" journalOrPublisher="Science Press, Beijing, China" pageId="0" pageNumber="179" refId="B7" refString="Dai, AY, 1999. Fauna Sinica: ArthropodaCrustaceaMalacostracaDecapodaParathelphusidaePotamidae. Science Press, Beijing, China" title="Fauna Sinica: ArthropodaCrustaceaMalacostracaDecapodaParathelphusidaePotamidae." year="1999">Dai 1999</bibRefCitation>
); anterolateral margin ~ 2 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
as long as external orbital outer margin (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Sinopotamon fukienense, male, 23.2 x 29.0 mm, NNU 11 B- 211121 SF 1 A dorsal overall view ventral B view of anterior thoracic sternum and pleon C frontal view D ventral view of sterno-pleonal cavity with right G 1 in situ (left G 1 removed). Scale bars: 1.0 cm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1112.85278.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/715097" pageId="0" pageNumber="179">2A</figureCitation>
; cf. 
<bibRefCitation author="Dai, AY" journalOrPublisher="Acta Zoologica Sinica" pageId="0" pageNumber="179" pagination="243 - 249" refId="B8" refString="Dai, AY, Chen, GX, 1979. On the freshwater crabs from Fujian Province. Acta Zoologica Sinica 25: 243 - 249" title="On the freshwater crabs from Fujian Province." volume="25" year="1979">Dai and Chen 1979</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Li, YS" journalOrPublisher="Wuyi Science Journal" pageId="0" pageNumber="179" pagination="141 - 146" refId="B19" refString="Li, YS, Lin, JX, Cheng, YZ, Tang, JH, 1985. A new species of Sinopotamon crab harbouring metacercariae of lung flukes from the Wuyishan National Reserve, Fujian (Decapoda: Sinopotamonidae). Wuyi Science Journal 5: 141 - 146" title="A new species of Sinopotamon crab harbouring metacercariae of lung flukes from the Wuyishan National Reserve, Fujian (Decapoda: Sinopotamonidae)." volume="5" year="1985">Li et al. 1985</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Dai, AY" journalOrPublisher="Science Press, Beijing, China" pageId="0" pageNumber="179" refId="B7" refString="Dai, AY, 1999. Fauna Sinica: ArthropodaCrustaceaMalacostracaDecapodaParathelphusidaePotamidae. Science Press, Beijing, China" title="Fauna Sinica: ArthropodaCrustaceaMalacostracaDecapodaParathelphusidaePotamidae." year="1999">Dai 1999</bibRefCitation>
); G1 terminal segment tapering, tip directed outwards (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Sinopotamon fukienense, male, 23.2 x 29.0 mm, NNU 11 B- 211121 SF 1 A dorsal overall view ventral B view of anterior thoracic sternum and pleon C frontal view D ventral view of sterno-pleonal cavity with right G 1 in situ (left G 1 removed). Scale bars: 1.0 cm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1112.85278.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/715097" pageId="0" pageNumber="179">2D</figureCitation>
; cf. 
<bibRefCitation author="Dai, AY" journalOrPublisher="Acta Zoologica Sinica" pageId="0" pageNumber="179" pagination="243 - 249" refId="B8" refString="Dai, AY, Chen, GX, 1979. On the freshwater crabs from Fujian Province. Acta Zoologica Sinica 25: 243 - 249" title="On the freshwater crabs from Fujian Province." volume="25" year="1979">Dai and Chen 1979</bibRefCitation>
: fig. 2(1), (2); 
<bibRefCitation author="Li, YS" journalOrPublisher="Wuyi Science Journal" pageId="0" pageNumber="179" pagination="141 - 146" refId="B19" refString="Li, YS, Lin, JX, Cheng, YZ, Tang, JH, 1985. A new species of Sinopotamon crab harbouring metacercariae of lung flukes from the Wuyishan National Reserve, Fujian (Decapoda: Sinopotamonidae). Wuyi Science Journal 5: 141 - 146" title="A new species of Sinopotamon crab harbouring metacercariae of lung flukes from the Wuyishan National Reserve, Fujian (Decapoda: Sinopotamonidae)." volume="5" year="1985">Li et al. 1985</bibRefCitation>
: figs 1, 2; 
<bibRefCitation author="Dai, AY" journalOrPublisher="Science Press, Beijing, China" pageId="0" pageNumber="179" refId="B7" refString="Dai, AY, 1999. Fauna Sinica: ArthropodaCrustaceaMalacostracaDecapodaParathelphusidaePotamidae. Science Press, Beijing, China" title="Fauna Sinica: ArthropodaCrustaceaMalacostracaDecapodaParathelphusidaePotamidae." year="1999">Dai 1999</bibRefCitation>
: fig. 136(3), (4)), not reaching suture sternites 5/6 (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Sinopotamon fukienense, male, 23.2 x 29.0 mm, NNU 11 B- 211121 SF 1 A dorsal overall view ventral B view of anterior thoracic sternum and pleon C frontal view D ventral view of sterno-pleonal cavity with right G 1 in situ (left G 1 removed). Scale bars: 1.0 cm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1112.85278.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/715097" pageId="0" pageNumber="179">2D</figureCitation>
; cf. 
<bibRefCitation author="Dai, AY" journalOrPublisher="Acta Zoologica Sinica" pageId="0" pageNumber="179" pagination="243 - 249" refId="B8" refString="Dai, AY, Chen, GX, 1979. On the freshwater crabs from Fujian Province. Acta Zoologica Sinica 25: 243 - 249" title="On the freshwater crabs from Fujian Province." volume="25" year="1979">Dai and Chen 1979</bibRefCitation>
: fig. 2(1), (2); 
<bibRefCitation author="Li, YS" journalOrPublisher="Wuyi Science Journal" pageId="0" pageNumber="179" pagination="141 - 146" refId="B19" refString="Li, YS, Lin, JX, Cheng, YZ, Tang, JH, 1985. A new species of Sinopotamon crab harbouring metacercariae of lung flukes from the Wuyishan National Reserve, Fujian (Decapoda: Sinopotamonidae). Wuyi Science Journal 5: 141 - 146" title="A new species of Sinopotamon crab harbouring metacercariae of lung flukes from the Wuyishan National Reserve, Fujian (Decapoda: Sinopotamonidae)." volume="5" year="1985">Li et al. 1985</bibRefCitation>
: figs 1, 2; 
<bibRefCitation author="Dai, AY" journalOrPublisher="Science Press, Beijing, China" pageId="0" pageNumber="179" refId="B7" refString="Dai, AY, 1999. Fauna Sinica: ArthropodaCrustaceaMalacostracaDecapodaParathelphusidaePotamidae. Science Press, Beijing, China" title="Fauna Sinica: ArthropodaCrustaceaMalacostracaDecapodaParathelphusidaePotamidae." year="1999">Dai 1999</bibRefCitation>
: fig. 136(3), (4)), subterminal segment to terminal segment ratio ~ 2.5 (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Sinopotamon fukienense, male, 23.2 x 29.0 mm, NNU 11 B- 211121 SF 1 A dorsal overall view ventral B view of anterior thoracic sternum and pleon C frontal view D ventral view of sterno-pleonal cavity with right G 1 in situ (left G 1 removed). Scale bars: 1.0 cm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1112.85278.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/715097" pageId="0" pageNumber="179">2D</figureCitation>
; cf. 
<bibRefCitation author="Dai, AY" journalOrPublisher="Acta Zoologica Sinica" pageId="0" pageNumber="179" pagination="243 - 249" refId="B8" refString="Dai, AY, Chen, GX, 1979. On the freshwater crabs from Fujian Province. Acta Zoologica Sinica 25: 243 - 249" title="On the freshwater crabs from Fujian Province." volume="25" year="1979">Dai and Chen 1979</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Li, YS" journalOrPublisher="Wuyi Science Journal" pageId="0" pageNumber="179" pagination="141 - 146" refId="B19" refString="Li, YS, Lin, JX, Cheng, YZ, Tang, JH, 1985. A new species of Sinopotamon crab harbouring metacercariae of lung flukes from the Wuyishan National Reserve, Fujian (Decapoda: Sinopotamonidae). Wuyi Science Journal 5: 141 - 146" title="A new species of Sinopotamon crab harbouring metacercariae of lung flukes from the Wuyishan National Reserve, Fujian (Decapoda: Sinopotamonidae)." volume="5" year="1985">Li et al. 1985</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Dai, AY" journalOrPublisher="Science Press, Beijing, China" pageId="0" pageNumber="179" refId="B7" refString="Dai, AY, 1999. Fauna Sinica: ArthropodaCrustaceaMalacostracaDecapodaParathelphusidaePotamidae. Science Press, Beijing, China" title="Fauna Sinica: ArthropodaCrustaceaMalacostracaDecapodaParathelphusidaePotamidae." year="1999">Dai 1999</bibRefCitation>
); female pleon subovate, vulvae ovate (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figure 3. Sinopotamon fukienense, female, 22.5 x 29.0 mm, NNU 11 B- 211219 SF 14 A ventral view of pleon B ventral view showing female vulvae. Scale bars: 1.0 cm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1112.85278.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/715098" pageId="0" pageNumber="179">3</figureCitation>
; cf. 
<bibRefCitation author="Dai, AY" journalOrPublisher="Acta Zoologica Sinica" pageId="0" pageNumber="179" pagination="243 - 249" refId="B8" refString="Dai, AY, Chen, GX, 1979. On the freshwater crabs from Fujian Province. Acta Zoologica Sinica 25: 243 - 249" title="On the freshwater crabs from Fujian Province." volume="25" year="1979">Dai and Chen 1979</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Li, YS" journalOrPublisher="Wuyi Science Journal" pageId="0" pageNumber="179" pagination="141 - 146" refId="B19" refString="Li, YS, Lin, JX, Cheng, YZ, Tang, JH, 1985. A new species of Sinopotamon crab harbouring metacercariae of lung flukes from the Wuyishan National Reserve, Fujian (Decapoda: Sinopotamonidae). Wuyi Science Journal 5: 141 - 146" title="A new species of Sinopotamon crab harbouring metacercariae of lung flukes from the Wuyishan National Reserve, Fujian (Decapoda: Sinopotamonidae)." volume="5" year="1985">Li et al. 1985</bibRefCitation>
: figs 5, 6; 
<bibRefCitation author="Dai, AY" journalOrPublisher="Science Press, Beijing, China" pageId="0" pageNumber="179" refId="B7" refString="Dai, AY, 1999. Fauna Sinica: ArthropodaCrustaceaMalacostracaDecapodaParathelphusidaePotamidae. Science Press, Beijing, China" title="Fauna Sinica: ArthropodaCrustaceaMalacostracaDecapodaParathelphusidaePotamidae." year="1999">Dai 1999</bibRefCitation>
: fig. 136(7), (8)). Therefore, it is most likely that the holotype of 
<taxonomicName genus="S." lsidName="S. wuyiensis" pageId="0" pageNumber="179" rank="species" species="wuyiensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="179">S. wuyiensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a rare gynandromorphic specimen (Youzhu Cheng, pers. comm.), rather than a representative of a new species. Therefore, 
<taxonomicName genus="S." lsidName="S. wuyiensis" pageId="0" pageNumber="179" rank="species" species="wuyiensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="179">S. wuyiensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is herein synonymized with 
<taxonomicName genus="S." lsidName="S. fukienense" pageId="0" pageNumber="179" rank="species" species="fukienense">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="179">S. fukienense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
